  <summary date="2012-09-24T20:36:29Z" status="Passed House without amendment">(This measure has not been amended since it was introduced. The summary of that version is repeated here.)

Buffett Rule Act of 2012 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow taxpayers to donate an amount (not less than $1), in addition to any tax owed, which shall be deposited in the general fund of the Treasury and transferred to an account used to reduce the public debt.&#160; Requires such donation to be designated on&#160;a taxpayer's income tax return at the time such return is filed.</summary>
